      • showNextPage

        public final void showNextPage()
        • Applications will call wizBehavior.showNextPage().
        • Once the pageIdToBeShown is finalized based on the wizard definition. createPage is called, if the page has not been displayed previously.
        • Page is shown.
        • If the page is already shown during the the lifecycle of the wizard, then it is interpreted as a call to showPreviousPage.

      • pageBeingDisposed

        public abstract void pageBeingDisposed(java.lang.String wizardPageFormId)
        This method is called when the wizard page is about to be disposed. The wizard page is disposed when one traverses back to the previous in a wizard.
        Parameters:
        wizardPageFormId - The page id of the page going to be disposed.

      • initPage

        public void initPage(java.lang.String wizardPageFormId)
        This method is called when a wizard page is about to be shown for the first time. Sub classes should extend this method to do initial processing and also to populate the page with data. Default behavior does nothing. NOTE: This method will be called only when a explicit page behavior has not been provided with the page being shown.

      • pageAboutToBeShown

        public void pageAboutToBeShown(java.lang.String wizardPageFormId)
        This method is called when a wizard page is about to be shown. NOTE: This method will not be called when the page is shown for the first time.
        See Also:
        Default behavior does nothing.

      • handleTaskCompletion

        public void handleTaskCompletion()
        This method is called when the current task is completed. Completion is assumed when showNextPage() is called and there are no more wizard transitions to be performed. Default behavior does nothing.

      • createChildWizard

        public YRCWizard createChildWizard(java.lang.String wizardPageFormId,
                                   org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Composite pnlRoot,
                                   YRCWizardContext wizardContext)
        The method is called internally when showNextPage is called. The child Classs should
        • Override this method.
        • Initializes child Wizard and return it
        • Set Child Wizard's Task Id to YRCWizardContext and pass this context to YRCWizard Constructor
        Since:
        Camden Town
        See Also:
        YRCWizardContext.setChildTaskId(String), YRCWizard.YRCWizard(String, Composite, YRCWizardContext, Object, int)

      • handleChildTaskCompletion

        public void handleChildTaskCompletion()
        If showNextPage is called by last page of Child wizard, Next page is called for a Parent wizard according to Wizard definition. In a simple wizard scenario handleTaskCompletion is called, incase of child Wizard this method is called before calling Parent wizard's showNextPage. NOTE: this method will be called only for Child Wizard.
        Since:
        Camden Town
        See Also:
        handleTaskCompletion()
